> [eeekz](#comment_1_14oc4TdKFZgv764PavBYPQc15qQgmd7jgL): “Deep web” and “dark net” are now meaningless media terms to use in clickbait headers and vain sensationalist articles. The fact that seemingly technical people participate in such bullshit discussions is a downer. Go read some papers on Freenet or Tor to understand how little can actually be made anonymous and private.

When the term Deep Web first came about it had a different meaning than media spin has given it now. It originally simply mean a part of the web that wasn't easily accessible to people that did already know it existed, not necessarily supposedly anonymous networks like TOR. Like a website that purposely didn't list it's self in search engines and the like.
